codes.code: argmax 'This is a quiz of your ability to understand Latin vocabulary. For each problem there is a ~ character in the text and your job is to figure out what word should be replaced by the ~. Provide the answer only. 1. Servus improbus ā dominō suō abit = Servus improbus ~ ~ ~ Choose from this set of possible answers [ dominum suum relinquit, ā|ab dominīs suīs nōn abeunt, tabernam relinquunt, Aemiliam et puerōs relinquit, ā pāstōre suō abit, pāstōrem nōn relinquit, ab ovibus albīs abit, ovem et canem relinquit] [ANSWER]' from 'openai/text-davinci-003' where ANSWER in [ 'dominum suum relinquit', 'ā|ab dominīs suīs nōn abeunt', 'tabernam relinquunt', 'Aemiliam et puerōs relinquit', 'ā pāstōre suō abit', 'pāstōrem nōn relinquit', 'ab ovibus albīs abit', 'ovem et canem relinquit']
